{"parentUuid":"0d99dc4e-930b-4dac-8327-27bcac1cd544","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adfd61437541dd82d","message":{"id":"gen-1775401667-z79X3EcSHaDrYuqzxF7u","type":"message","role":"assistant","container":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm online and ready, Trevor. Here is my self-check on those patterns:\n\n1. **Catch-and-swallow without re-throw** -- The caller has no idea something failed and will continue operating on stale or missing data, creating downstream bugs far from the root cause. Better pattern: log with context, then re-throw or return a Result that forces the caller to handle the failure explicitly.\n\n2. **Fetch without checking `response.ok`** -- You could successfully parse JSON from a 404 or 500 error body and silently treat an error page as valid data. Better pattern: always check `response.ok`, log and throw with status details when it fails, then handle or propagate.\n\n3. **Optional chain returning `undefined` silently** -- Downstream code gets `undefined` values that propagate through the system, corrupting state or UI with no error trail to trace. Better pattern: check for undefined/null explicitly, log the missing value with context, and either throw or present the user with a clear recovery path.\n\nI am ready for work -- assign me a task whenever the boss has something ready.","citations":null}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.6-plus-04-02:free","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"inference_geo":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null,"speed":"standard"},"provider":"Alibaba"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"f5966fe6-b549-4aa3-8b39-2e9f5e1d94f9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:07:59.638Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/klauskollerkroeff","sessionId":"3689e43b-d83e-4e2a-9aee-c6f823853854","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"indexed-pondering-leaf"}
